    "plan_content": "## Plan Ready\n\nHere's what I found and what I'm proposing:\n\n### Codebase Analysis\n\n- All specialized handlers live in `common/chat.cpp` as `static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_XXX(...)` functions\n- The last existing handler (`common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`) ends at **line 1517**; detection dispatch is in `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` starting at **line 1634**\n- `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` already exists — no `chat.h` changes needed\n- The Ministral 3 handler is safely distinguished by requiring `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` to be *present* in the template source\n\n### Two changes to `common/chat.cpp`\n\n**Change 1 — New handler** (after line 1517, before `namespace workaround`):\n- Builds `data.prompt` starting with `tmpl.bos_token()` (`<s>`)\n- Iterates `inputs.messages`: holds system content in `pending_system`, prepends it with `\\n` to the first user message\n- Wraps user turns: `[INST] {content} [/INST]`\n- Appends assistant turns: ` {content}</s>` (leading space matches the spec)\n- Sets `data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY`; no grammar/parser needed\n\n**Change 2 — Detection block** (just before `return std::nullopt;` at line 1690):\n- Triggers when template source contains `[INST]` **and** `[/INST]` **and does not** contain `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`\n- Placed last to let all more-specific handlers (Ministral 3, GPT-OSS, Functionary, Kimi K2, LFM2, GigaChat) take priority first",
